briefdescription.para: Action handler for the "About us" button.

para.verbatim:
Action steps: - Starts a background thread. - Uses ReportService.getCashierInfo() to retrieve cashier data from the backend and logs the number of cashiers found. - Opens the Info window in the Event Dispatch Thread. - Closes the current Cashier window.
Any error retrieving data is logged to the standard error stream but does not prevent opening the Info window.

Any error while checking the status is logged to the standard error stream but does not prevent opening the menu window.

briefdescription.para: Login window for authenticating cashiers.

para.verbatim:
It is displayed after a successful login with role CASHIER. Shows a Swing form that lets cashiers: - access to the general menu window used to register orders. - access to the "About us" information window. - log out and return to the login window.
Additionally, some actions perform background calls to the backend using ReportService to: - retrieve cashier information. - check the menu or system status.
